engineCMS::accessControl()

Description
    public bool engineCMS::accessControl(string $action [, bool $value = NULL [, bool $state = FALSE]])
    Performs a specific action based upon the action parameter.

Parameters
    action
	A valid string value of "debugListAll", "existsTest", "build", "denyAll", "allowAll" or "clear"

	debugListAll calls var_dump() on the internal access control list and returns TRUE.

	existsTest checks the value stored in the value parameter.  If it contains a value, that value is assigned to the internal accessExistsTest, 		and the calling function returns TRUE.  Otherwise, the calling function returns FALSE.

    value
	TRUE, FALSE or void (when calling exit).

    state

Return Values
    
